# BPSK Communication System Laboratory

## Overview

This laboratory demonstrated Binary Phase Shift Keying (BPSK), one of the fundamental digital modulation techniques used in modern communication systems. The lab explored signal generation, transmission, and recovery.

## Technologies

- BPSK
- Digital Communications
- Signal Processing

## Skills Developed

- Digital modulation
- Signal analysis
- Communication system design

## Learning Outcome

This laboratory helped connect theoretical communication concepts with practical digital signal transmission techniques.
